<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-06-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-06-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="942" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d942">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Graves</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Stockholm</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-06-07"><hi rend="italic">June 7,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Graves reports that the cabinet of Norway has been unanimously
                            authorized by the Norwegian Storthing to conduct the administration of
                            the Kingdom of Norway with regent authority. A friendly address was sent
                            to King Oscar by the Storthing, asking him to designate a member of the
                            Bernadotte dynasty to ascend the throne of Norway. Arctander has been
                            appointed Norwegian minister for foreign affairs.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>